1
00:02:10,376 --> 00:02:12,180
[ Bird screeching. Loud ]

2
00:02:16,648 --> 00:02:17,509
Shush.

3
00:02:19,149 --> 00:02:19,821
Polly.

4
00:02:29,114 --> 00:02:30,035
Sahib Wales.

5
00:02:30,854 --> 00:02:32,755
You should not have come.

6
00:02:33,470 --> 00:02:34,478
In this room.

7
00:02:36,627 --> 00:02:37,580
My dear man.

8
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:40,048
Ramdaz.

9
00:02:40,674 --> 00:02:42,638
Here is ten rupees.

10
00:02:45,274 --> 00:02:46,118
It is yours.

11
00:02:47,261 --> 00:02:51,163
If you leave me alone in
this room for ten minutes.

12
00:02:52,297 --> 00:02:52,883
No.

13
00:02:53,888 --> 00:02:55,105
Maybe the commissioner ..

14
00:02:55,468 --> 00:02:57,227
Will blame me. Ramdaz.

15
00:02:58,252 --> 00:03:03,070
I am more interested in finding
out who murdered your master ..

16
00:03:03,582 --> 00:03:04,575
Than the police.

17
00:03:04,895 --> 00:03:06,828
The commissioner say to me: 'Ramdaz'.

18
00:03:07,391 --> 00:03:09,484
'Everything stay same here'.

19
00:03:10,156 --> 00:03:12,949
'Until the chief inspector, he come'.

20
00:03:16,180 --> 00:03:17,330
Stand over there.

21
00:03:21,355 --> 00:03:22,604
Stand there.

22
00:03:28,825 --> 00:03:29,746
Sit down.

23
00:03:32,754 --> 00:03:34,602
A stupid mess.

24
00:03:35,249 --> 00:03:36,136
Stupid.

25
00:03:38,598 --> 00:03:39,442
Ramdaz.

26
00:03:40,253 --> 00:03:42,404
I say, can't you understand ..

27
00:03:45,679 --> 00:03:46,494
Now listen.

28
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:49,032
I'll give you 20 rupees, 30 rupees.

29
00:03:49,523 --> 00:03:50,871
Will you do what I ask?

30
00:03:51,308 --> 00:03:53,222
Will you please do what I ask of you?

31
00:04:01,748 --> 00:04:04,246
Ramdaz, I could strangle you.

32
00:04:14,736 --> 00:04:15,408
I say.

33
00:04:15,836 --> 00:04:17,662
I say, Commissioner Grimshaw.
Are you there?

34
00:04:18,174 --> 00:04:20,047
Mr Wales, I am thoroughly exasperated.

35
00:04:20,862 --> 00:04:23,894
You have not only disobeyed police
orders but you're becoming a pest.

36
00:04:24,278 --> 00:04:24,950
I see.

37
00:04:25,607 --> 00:04:26,365
See here.

38
00:04:27,625 --> 00:04:28,672
Hang it all.

39
00:04:31,374 --> 00:04:32,075
Listen.

40
00:04:33,185 --> 00:04:38,814
I am positive that I can identify
the woman who killed Spencer Lee.

41
00:04:39,998 --> 00:04:40,985
Explain yourself.

42
00:04:41,966 --> 00:04:45,529
No. It would be most unwise
to mention her name.

43
00:04:46,909 --> 00:04:49,845
You see. She is very highly connected.

44
00:04:50,422 --> 00:04:51,542
In official circles.

45
00:04:52,196 --> 00:04:53,513
Careful, Mr Wales.

46
00:04:54,157 --> 00:04:55,688
You're treading on dangerous ground.

47
00:04:56,581 --> 00:04:58,627
It is best that you wait there.
We'll be right along.

48
00:05:00,411 --> 00:05:02,696
Delzante. This man Wales is insane.

49
00:05:03,550 --> 00:05:04,981
Now he intimates it was a woman.

50
00:05:05,585 --> 00:05:07,144
Highly connected in official circles.

51
00:05:13,014 --> 00:05:16,260
Highly connected in official circles?

52
00:05:21,508 --> 00:05:22,552
These records show.

53
00:05:23,611 --> 00:05:25,603
That this woman was heavily veiled.

54
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:27,574
Tommy-rot. All Tommy-rot.

55
00:05:28,247 --> 00:05:31,176
Most of Spencer Lee's women
callers were heavily veiled.

56
00:05:31,834 --> 00:05:33,607
Most of them, married women.

57
00:05:34,877 --> 00:05:37,127
Yet, immediately after her departure ..

58
00:05:38,011 --> 00:05:40,122
The crime was discovered.

59
00:05:40,570 --> 00:05:43,346
Yes. Edward Wales arrived at the house
just as the woman was leaving.

60
00:05:43,922 --> 00:05:46,171
He found Lee on the floor with
a knife wound in his back.

61
00:05:46,845 --> 00:05:48,793
He died in Wales' arms.
Without speaking.

62
00:05:52,661 --> 00:05:53,820
Let us be moving along.

63
00:05:54,344 --> 00:05:55,817
I would like to speak with this ..

64
00:05:56,116 --> 00:05:57,867
Mr Wales.
- Just a moment please.

65
00:05:59,866 --> 00:06:01,764
Get me Sir Roscoe Crosby
at the residency.

66
00:06:02,196 --> 00:06:04,682
You found no fingerprints of this woman?
- No.

67
00:06:05,448 --> 00:06:08,511
Although tea had been served
her cup had not been touched.

68
00:06:10,211 --> 00:06:11,026
Sir Roscoe?

69
00:06:11,671 --> 00:06:13,059
This is Commissioner Grimshaw.

70
00:06:13,686 --> 00:06:14,930
I wish to advise you, sir.

71
00:06:15,324 --> 00:06:18,426
That Inspector Delzante of the
Criminal Investigation department.

72
00:06:18,839 --> 00:06:21,330
Arrived in Calcutta this afternoon
and sends his respect, sir.

73
00:06:21,809 --> 00:06:22,948
Thank him, Grimshaw.

74
00:06:23,371 --> 00:06:27,182
And assure him that my office is at his
service for any assistance he requires.

75
00:06:28,138 --> 00:06:30,519
Here. You have missed one.
- So I have.

76
00:06:30,914 --> 00:06:32,564
A very good one too.
- Rather.

77
00:06:33,475 --> 00:06:34,491
That was Grimshaw.

78
00:06:35,408 --> 00:06:39,071
Inspector Delzante of the Criminal
Investigation Department has arrived.

79
00:06:39,524 --> 00:06:40,339
Sir Roscoe.

80
00:06:40,826 --> 00:06:43,648
I know I am wrong, and I just
cannot explain my feelings.

81
00:06:44,235 --> 00:06:45,943
But at times I find myself hoping.

82
00:06:46,349 --> 00:06:48,399
I hope they never find the culprit.

83
00:06:48,837 --> 00:06:49,954
Come, my dear.

84
00:06:50,651 --> 00:06:52,096
I admit he was a bit of a rotter.

85
00:06:52,691 --> 00:06:54,169
But you mustn't feel that way.

86
00:06:54,575 --> 00:06:56,694
Father, now please
don't start preaching.

87
00:06:57,023 --> 00:06:58,866
Mother wasn't thinking
of Spencer's morals.

88
00:06:59,182 --> 00:07:00,766
Were you, darling?
- No.

89
00:07:01,295 --> 00:07:02,597
I was thinking of the woman.

90
00:07:03,509 --> 00:07:04,333
And Roscoe.

91
00:07:04,749 --> 00:07:07,595
I have a feeling that it
was that veiled woman.

92
00:07:08,822 --> 00:07:10,428
And I dread learning who she is.

93
00:07:10,757 --> 00:07:11,782
Nellie O'Neill.

94
00:07:14,163 --> 00:07:14,982
I say.

95
00:07:15,375 --> 00:07:17,012
Do you think something could be wrong?

96
00:07:17,778 --> 00:07:18,479
Nellie.

97
00:07:20,633 --> 00:07:21,992
Nellie, wait a minute. Please.

98
00:07:26,131 --> 00:07:27,089
Nellie O'Neill.

99
00:07:30,964 --> 00:07:32,420
You know, you are stubborn.

100
00:07:32,986 --> 00:07:34,906
You are just plain stubborn.

101
00:07:36,492 --> 00:07:37,324
Richard.

102
00:07:38,072 --> 00:07:40,630
When a woman loves a man
as much as I love you ..

103
00:07:41,368 --> 00:07:42,825
It is hard to say 'no'.

104
00:07:43,558 --> 00:07:44,887
Nellie, I don't want you to.

105
00:07:45,197 --> 00:07:48,027
There's nothing that would make me
happier than to marry you, but ..

106
00:07:48,728 --> 00:07:49,457
I can't.

107
00:07:49,699 --> 00:07:51,043
What is it then, dear?

108
00:07:51,791 --> 00:07:52,614
Everything.

109
00:07:53,389 --> 00:07:56,227
Do you realize you don't even
know who I am or what I am?

110
00:07:56,819 --> 00:07:58,406
Nonsense, darling. I don't care.

111
00:07:58,810 --> 00:07:59,928
Don't you see, dear?

112
00:08:01,113 --> 00:08:03,456
There is a great difference between us.

113
00:08:06,021 --> 00:08:07,964
So that's the bee in your bonnet.

114
00:08:09,859 --> 00:08:13,540
You think because you're my mother's
secretary that you shouldn't marry me.

115
00:08:15,178 --> 00:08:16,222
Nellie, look at me.

116
00:08:17,784 --> 00:08:18,485
Nellie.

117
00:08:20,895 --> 00:08:22,731
That can't make any
difference to us, dear.

118
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:24,576
It never will make a difference.

119
00:08:25,065 --> 00:08:27,598
You don't seem to understand.
- Darling, don't be silly.

120
00:08:28,783 --> 00:08:31,587
You come along with me and
we'll settle that once and for all.

121
00:08:32,059 --> 00:08:33,246
Do as I say. Come along.

122
00:08:33,782 --> 00:08:36,745
Nellie is a brick, and I shall
jolly well cherish her as a sister.

123
00:08:38,046 --> 00:08:41,080
I suppose we shall have to be
reconciled to Richard's choice.

124
00:08:43,155 --> 00:08:44,898
After all, it's really his wedding.

125
00:08:45,478 --> 00:08:46,465
Well, rather.

126
00:08:46,827 --> 00:08:48,110
Roscoe, you're an old dear.

127
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:49,416
Top hole, Richard.

128
00:08:49,777 --> 00:08:51,536
The family sanctions
your choice of a wife.

129
00:08:52,306 --> 00:08:55,274
Thanks, Helen. Awfully nice of you but I
feel you put the cart before the horse.

130
00:08:55,606 --> 00:08:56,850
What do you mean, Richard?

131
00:08:57,242 --> 00:08:58,384
Mother.
- What is it?

132
00:08:58,606 --> 00:09:00,508
Nellie is all fussed-up
because we've got money.

133
00:09:01,727 --> 00:09:02,885
She thinks that I am ..

134
00:09:03,619 --> 00:09:06,098
You know, what they call in
books, 'marrying beneath me'.

135
00:09:06,903 --> 00:09:08,927
Suppose you listen to an old woman.
- Old?

136
00:09:09,330 --> 00:09:10,698
Well, old enough.

137
00:09:11,305 --> 00:09:12,733
Now then. Listen.

138
00:09:13,299 --> 00:09:14,715
When I married Richard's father.

139
00:09:15,175 --> 00:09:16,305
I was a schoolteacher.

140
00:09:16,641 --> 00:09:18,759
And he was a youngest son.
A captain in the army.

141
00:09:19,565 --> 00:09:20,786
We had no money.

142
00:09:21,235 --> 00:09:22,553
But we were awfully in love.

143
00:09:23,366 --> 00:09:24,959
Just for the sake of argument.

144
00:09:25,326 --> 00:09:26,799
Suppose I had taken your attitude.

145
00:09:27,918 --> 00:09:28,762
Why, Nellie.

146
00:09:29,279 --> 00:09:31,405
We should have missed
many years of happiness.

147
00:09:33,128 --> 00:09:34,926
And we still rather like each other.

148
00:09:36,214 --> 00:09:37,827
Now if you want my real opinion.

149
00:09:38,237 --> 00:09:40,370
I think Richard's
pretty lucky to get you.

150
00:09:40,757 --> 00:09:43,009
Yes, my dear. Take us as you find us.

151
00:09:43,535 --> 00:09:45,330
And we'll all try to be happy.

152
00:10:05,553 --> 00:10:06,425
Now the thug.

153
00:10:07,002 --> 00:10:09,160
Has his victim at his mercy.

154
00:10:09,621 --> 00:10:11,253
Release me. You're strangling me.

155
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:16,162
All that beastly thing lacks
is a mouth with fangs.

156
00:10:21,869 --> 00:10:22,941
I say, doctor.

157
00:10:23,312 --> 00:10:25,348
The professor seems
a bit of a thug himself.

158
00:10:25,866 --> 00:10:28,448
Yes. He gave a bit of a
realistic demonstration.

159
00:10:30,809 --> 00:10:31,754
And so.

160
00:10:32,218 --> 00:10:35,422
That's the method the thugs use
to remove their enemies, eh?

161
00:10:36,034 --> 00:10:36,830
Yes.

162
00:10:37,680 --> 00:10:39,683
Which proves to me conclusively.

163
00:10:40,370 --> 00:10:43,144
That they had no hand.

164
00:10:44,261 --> 00:10:46,295
In the killing of Mr Lee.

165
00:10:48,691 --> 00:10:52,192
You don't think that Lee's articles
attacking the Thugee cult ..

166
00:10:53,068 --> 00:10:54,339
Prompted his death?

167
00:10:56,689 --> 00:10:57,542
A thug.

168
00:10:58,733 --> 00:11:00,816
Never spills blood.

169
00:11:01,782 --> 00:11:04,970
You forget the veiled charmer, doctor.
She is my choice.

170
00:11:05,377 --> 00:11:07,003
No. I haven't forgotten the woman.

171
00:11:07,574 --> 00:11:09,795
Now that Delzante is
here for the investigation.

172
00:11:10,434 --> 00:11:13,787
I feel pretty sure that her
identity will soon be disclosed.

173
00:11:14,237 --> 00:11:15,024
Look here.

174
00:11:15,488 --> 00:11:17,704
To aid the crown in its
search for the guilty one.

175
00:11:18,361 --> 00:11:20,910
I propose a whiskey and soda.

176
00:11:21,425 --> 00:11:22,670
And a rubber of bridge.

177
00:11:23,905 --> 00:11:26,003
A charming idea. And Nellie.

178
00:11:26,557 --> 00:11:27,915
See if you can find Richard.

179
00:11:28,307 --> 00:11:30,432
He is probably with
Sir Roscoe and Mr Wales.

180
00:11:31,695 --> 00:11:33,600
I told her it would be
a jolly good idea.

181
00:11:34,003 --> 00:11:35,448
Surely, Howard. You are spoofing.

182
00:11:35,887 --> 00:11:37,440
I grant you it's a bit grotesque.

183
00:11:37,889 --> 00:11:38,876
But nevertheless.

184
00:11:39,476 --> 00:11:42,117
Edward Wales has prevailed
upon Lady Crosby.

185
00:11:42,660 --> 00:11:45,054
To allow that spirit medium or ..

186
00:11:46,073 --> 00:11:48,222
Fortune teller or whatever you call it.

187
00:11:48,628 --> 00:11:51,859
To give a seance here tonight.
- That would be perfectly thrilling.

188
00:11:52,331 --> 00:11:53,688
A marvelous idea.
- I see.

189
00:11:54,193 --> 00:11:56,742
So tonight we are to dabble
in witchcraft and occultism?

190
00:11:57,419 --> 00:11:59,647
If she is a true medium
your eyes will be opened.

191
00:12:00,419 --> 00:12:02,748
I attended a seance in
Berlin at Madam Bogarts.

192
00:12:03,494 --> 00:12:05,603
And through her spirit control.

193
00:12:06,247 --> 00:12:07,267
I conversed.

194
00:12:08,962 --> 00:12:10,448
With my dead mother.

195
00:12:11,704 --> 00:12:12,471
By Jove.

196
00:12:13,534 --> 00:12:14,697
I have an idea.

197
00:12:15,409 --> 00:12:18,086
We should call on the
spirit of Spencer Lee.

198
00:12:18,911 --> 00:12:20,070
And I shall say to him.

199
00:12:20,419 --> 00:12:21,635
'Spencer, dear old chap'.

200
00:12:22,114 --> 00:12:23,490
'Tell us. Who killed you'?

201
00:12:24,355 --> 00:12:25,056
Howard.

202
00:12:25,774 --> 00:12:27,008
That's just sacrilege.

203
00:12:27,330 --> 00:12:28,843
It is not.
- Don't be silly.

204
00:12:29,165 --> 00:12:30,071
I am serious.

205
00:12:35,403 --> 00:12:37,736
But I don't understand what
you are talking about.

206
00:12:39,832 --> 00:12:41,893
Mr Wales, I demand an apology
for what you just said.

207
00:12:42,324 --> 00:12:43,483
Richard, calm yourself.

208
00:12:44,102 --> 00:12:46,141
Mr Wales, I am waiting.
- Richard.

209
00:12:47,256 --> 00:12:48,833
In your eyes my action is almost ..

210
00:12:49,679 --> 00:12:50,781
Indefensible.

211
00:12:51,471 --> 00:12:52,544
I am admitting that.

212
00:12:53,241 --> 00:12:55,323
But I have very good reasons for asking.

213
00:12:56,900 --> 00:12:57,993
What I am asking.

214
00:13:00,683 --> 00:13:01,498
Sir Roscoe.

215
00:13:02,193 --> 00:13:04,021
I've been your close
friend for many years.

216
00:13:04,648 --> 00:13:06,227
You've trusted me and believed in me.

217
00:13:06,924 --> 00:13:11,181
I ask you not to announce Richard's
engagement to Miss O'Neill tonight.

218
00:13:12,326 --> 00:13:13,113
After all.

219
00:13:13,841 --> 00:13:16,782
24 hours can't make any
difference, Richard.

220
00:13:17,700 --> 00:13:20,376
And it may save you all a
great deal of unhappiness.

221
00:13:20,873 --> 00:13:21,730
Mr Wales.

222
00:13:22,247 --> 00:13:23,955
I don't know what you will discover.

223
00:13:24,312 --> 00:13:27,367
But it's nothing of which I am ashamed.
- Dear, you mustn't mind what he says.

224
00:13:27,691 --> 00:13:28,480
But I do.

225
00:13:28,933 --> 00:13:32,034
I know it's about my mother.
The most wonderful woman in the world.

226
00:13:32,401 --> 00:13:33,645
I won't have her attacked.

227
00:13:34,129 --> 00:13:35,001
Miss O'Neill.

228
00:13:35,710 --> 00:13:37,042
I don't know your mother.

229
00:13:38,028 --> 00:13:40,567
I've never even heard of her.
- Then you should explain ..

230
00:13:40,955 --> 00:13:43,843
Richard, I would rather be
shot than do what I am doing.

231
00:13:44,614 --> 00:13:47,203
But if I'm wrong I will come
to you gladly and say so.

232
00:13:47,798 --> 00:13:50,290
I'll apologise to Miss O'Neill
on my knees if she likes.

233
00:13:50,704 --> 00:13:52,406
Ned, I don't know
what this is all about.

234
00:13:53,596 --> 00:13:55,707
But knowing you as I do
I shall take your suggestion.

235
00:13:56,074 --> 00:13:57,536
But father ..
- Richard, please.

236
00:13:58,892 --> 00:13:59,822
But I warn you.

237
00:14:00,597 --> 00:14:03,978
Tomorrow I shall expect you to explain
everything to my entire satisfaction.

238
00:14:04,486 --> 00:14:06,665
You have my word, Sir Roscoe.
- Very well.

239
00:14:08,454 --> 00:14:10,665
I think we'll let the matter
rest for this evening and ..

240
00:14:11,048 --> 00:14:12,265
Join Lady Crosby.

241
00:14:12,768 --> 00:14:14,552
Dad, could I speak to you just a minute?

242
00:14:15,396 --> 00:14:16,829
Will you join the ladies, Ned.

243
00:14:17,543 --> 00:14:19,572
Dad, you can't ..
- Richard. Richard.

244
00:14:21,068 --> 00:14:23,315
Ned has evidently gone off on
the wrong foot somewhere.

245
00:14:24,635 --> 00:14:25,593
But don't worry.

246
00:14:26,072 --> 00:14:27,402
Things will right themselves.

247
00:14:27,934 --> 00:14:30,253
Have we time for another rubber?
- I don't think I would.

248
00:14:30,558 --> 00:14:31,790
They're here in a minute.

249
00:14:32,211 --> 00:14:34,393
I'm afraid this seance is
going to be a frightful bore.

250
00:14:35,216 --> 00:14:36,146
Don't say that.

251
00:14:36,527 --> 00:14:37,521
You needn't come.

252
00:14:38,233 --> 00:14:38,934
Edward.

253
00:14:39,206 --> 00:14:41,967
Madam La Grange, the fortune-teller
you sent the car for has arrived.

254
00:14:42,356 --> 00:14:43,856
May we see her now?
- Certainly.

255
00:14:44,417 --> 00:14:46,826
Chotee, ask Madam La Grange
to please come here.

256
00:14:47,269 --> 00:14:49,831
I say. Do you really suppose she
expects to be taken seriously?

257
00:14:50,825 --> 00:14:53,212
But then, if we don't laugh at
her we'll have no end of fun.

258
00:14:53,677 --> 00:14:56,175
I will rag her terribly. And she'll
never know it in all the world.

259
00:14:56,532 --> 00:14:57,201
Mary.

260
00:14:57,503 --> 00:14:58,576
I shouldn't do that.

261
00:14:58,887 --> 00:15:00,274
Edward says she's quite clever.

262
00:15:01,219 --> 00:15:04,193
The great Madam La Grange.
I'll bet you I can describe her.

263
00:15:04,802 --> 00:15:08,427
A tall dark-haired creature.
A regular adventuress. Am I right?

264
00:15:09,016 --> 00:15:11,796
She is the most remarkable
woman I have ever known.

265
00:15:12,832 --> 00:15:14,503
Madam Rosalie La Grange.

266
00:15:14,915 --> 00:15:16,339
Good evening to all of you.

267
00:15:16,786 --> 00:15:18,345
How do you do, Madam La Grange.

268
00:15:18,762 --> 00:15:20,517
Very well, thank you, ma'am.
- I'm glad.

269
00:15:21,492 --> 00:15:22,940
How are you, Mr Wales?

270
00:15:23,495 --> 00:15:25,877
To be sure, it was a grand
hack you sent for me.

271
00:15:26,243 --> 00:15:27,805
We wanted you to be comfortable.

272
00:15:28,328 --> 00:15:29,388
I was that.

273
00:15:29,923 --> 00:15:30,767
Do you know?

274
00:15:31,253 --> 00:15:33,206
When the Hindu gentleman came for me.

275
00:15:33,902 --> 00:15:36,274
I thought at first it
was the Rajah himself.

276
00:15:37,830 --> 00:15:39,217
I hope you were not frightened.

277
00:15:39,991 --> 00:15:41,117
Definitely not.

278
00:15:41,724 --> 00:15:44,742
I'd like to see the Hindu
that can frighten me.

279
00:15:45,234 --> 00:15:46,595
Nice boys them Hindus.

280
00:15:47,210 --> 00:15:49,114
And most of them good Christians.

281
00:15:50,044 --> 00:15:51,145
When they are asleep.

282
00:15:53,257 --> 00:15:54,343
Won't you sit down?

283
00:15:56,266 --> 00:15:57,253
Thank you, ma'am.

284
00:15:58,067 --> 00:16:00,050
Are you quite comfortable?
- I am.

285
00:16:01,161 --> 00:16:02,291
So, you tell fortunes?

286
00:16:03,439 --> 00:16:04,702
No, Miss. I do not.

287
00:16:05,437 --> 00:16:08,357
I get messages from them
that has passed on.

288
00:16:10,149 --> 00:16:14,008
I don't hold with the cards or
tea leaves or any of them tricks.

289
00:16:15,800 --> 00:16:16,444
Miss.

290
00:16:17,560 --> 00:16:18,945
Once in a while.

291
00:16:19,551 --> 00:16:20,622
I give advice.

292
00:16:22,892 --> 00:16:23,987
If I were you.

293
00:16:24,763 --> 00:16:28,403
I'd pay that bill of a thousand
rupees that you owe in the bazaar.

294
00:16:31,472 --> 00:16:33,954
We are expecting great things from
you tonight, Madam La Grange.

295
00:16:34,257 --> 00:16:36,074
How did you know I owed
a bill at the bazaar?

296
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:39,687
Well, you left the bill in
your bag in the hall.

297
00:16:40,627 --> 00:16:42,514
While I was waiting I read it.

298
00:16:43,076 --> 00:16:44,678
How did you know it was my bag?

299
00:16:45,004 --> 00:16:45,728
Sure.

300
00:16:46,041 --> 00:16:49,238
The stuff on the bag.
Matched that stuff on your dress.

301
00:16:52,141 --> 00:16:53,300
Then it's all trickery?

302
00:16:55,121 --> 00:16:56,555
It is now. And then it ain't.

303
00:16:57,258 --> 00:17:00,196
That is the sort of demonstration
we're going to get from you tonight?

304
00:17:00,726 --> 00:17:03,324
Didn't Mr Wales tell you?
- I've told them nothing.

305
00:17:04,172 --> 00:17:06,299
Well then, tell them now please.

306
00:17:07,524 --> 00:17:08,253
You see.

307
00:17:08,916 --> 00:17:10,269
As I told you some time ago.

308
00:17:10,989 --> 00:17:13,195
Madam La Grange has done things that ..

309
00:17:13,875 --> 00:17:15,362
That cannot be explained.

310
00:17:15,902 --> 00:17:17,490
When I asked her to come here tonight.

311
00:17:17,834 --> 00:17:20,078
She said she would
under certain conditions.

312
00:17:20,423 --> 00:17:23,008
You mean test conditions?
- Not exactly.

313
00:17:23,656 --> 00:17:26,919
What she said was, that no
money should pass between us.

314
00:17:27,389 --> 00:17:29,252
And that anything she
would do tonight ..

315
00:17:29,787 --> 00:17:31,021
Would be honest.

316
00:17:31,388 --> 00:17:32,985
You would not play us any tricks?

317
00:17:33,795 --> 00:17:35,288
If I do, I will tell you.

318
00:17:36,055 --> 00:17:38,966
Yes, of course. We understand
all about spirit rapping.

319
00:17:41,184 --> 00:17:42,826
Rather. That's old stuff.

320
00:17:43,560 --> 00:17:45,614
Well, what do you think of that?

321
00:17:46,031 --> 00:17:48,216
You have to be near a table
or something like that.

322
00:17:48,679 --> 00:17:49,529
And then.

323
00:17:50,107 --> 00:17:51,324
Maybe a chair.

324
00:17:51,844 --> 00:17:53,426
Or a desk would do.
- Yes?

325
00:17:53,834 --> 00:17:55,001
And then in the dark.

326
00:17:55,433 --> 00:17:57,184
Of course. In the dark.

327
00:17:58,191 --> 00:17:59,949
You get one rap for 'Yes'.

328
00:18:00,445 --> 00:18:01,633
And two for 'No'?

329
00:18:07,605 --> 00:18:09,220
Are there spirits near?

330
00:18:11,839 --> 00:18:13,047
Please don't laugh.

331
00:18:26,655 --> 00:18:27,897
Is it Laughing-Eyes?

332
00:18:29,650 --> 00:18:30,659
Are you happy?

333
00:18:33,251 --> 00:18:35,101
Is there someone here you don't like?

334
00:18:35,682 --> 00:18:36,526
[ One rap. ]

335
00:18:37,203 --> 00:18:38,139
A gentleman?

336
00:18:38,956 --> 00:18:39,983
[ Two raps. ]

337
00:18:40,533 --> 00:18:41,851
Dear, dear. A lady?

338
00:18:42,336 --> 00:18:43,180
[ One rap. ]

339
00:18:44,062 --> 00:18:45,082
Is it that one?

340
00:18:45,433 --> 00:18:46,277
[ One rap. ]

341
00:18:46,906 --> 00:18:48,279
Laughing-Eyes don't like you.

342
00:18:48,851 --> 00:18:49,666
Marvellous.

343
00:18:50,191 --> 00:18:51,822
The most wonderful thing I ever heard.

344
00:18:52,155 --> 00:18:53,914
But I don't think ..
- It can't be a trick.

345
00:18:54,261 --> 00:18:56,849
She stood right there and I
watched her hands every minute.

346
00:18:57,836 --> 00:19:00,088
Well, you watched the wrong end of me.

347
00:19:00,871 --> 00:19:02,661
I've got a wooden sole in my shoe.

348
00:19:03,223 --> 00:19:05,361
I do it with my big toe. Inside.

349
00:19:06,009 --> 00:19:06,795
Like this.

350
00:19:07,286 --> 00:19:08,411
[ Two raps. ]

351
00:19:10,490 --> 00:19:11,710
Sure. That time.

352
00:19:12,164 --> 00:19:14,662
So then, if we get any
messages it will be ..

353
00:19:15,030 --> 00:19:16,207
If we get any messages.

354
00:19:18,334 --> 00:19:20,577
Well, sir. I am telling
you the truth now.

355
00:19:21,642 --> 00:19:23,140
Most of the time it <i>is</i> tricks.

356
00:19:23,616 --> 00:19:24,732
But tonight.

357
00:19:25,234 --> 00:19:26,632
There will be no faking.

358
00:19:27,927 --> 00:19:30,960
I know I am a stranger to
all of you except Mr Wales.

359
00:19:31,782 --> 00:19:33,198
I don't know whose house I'm in.

360
00:19:33,532 --> 00:19:34,666
That's quite true.

361
00:19:34,990 --> 00:19:36,587
You gave her no hint of any kind?

362
00:19:37,107 --> 00:19:37,710
No.

363
00:19:38,186 --> 00:19:39,935
On my honour.
- Madam La Grange.

364
00:19:40,538 --> 00:19:41,153
Sir.

365
00:19:41,541 --> 00:19:43,520
I know a man who saw
this woman Paladino ..

366
00:19:44,114 --> 00:19:46,587
Lift a table just by
putting her hands on it.

367
00:19:53,500 --> 00:19:56,211
Would someone give me the
little card table over there.

368
00:19:57,217 --> 00:19:59,294
I suppose this is going to
be another fake trick.

369
00:20:02,740 --> 00:20:03,963
It can be done.

370
00:20:05,280 --> 00:20:06,279
It can be done.

371
00:20:07,405 --> 00:20:09,744
I don't know if I can
do it in the light.

372
00:20:10,951 --> 00:20:12,231
But if you want.

373
00:20:12,979 --> 00:20:14,375
I will try.
- Please do.

374
00:20:14,803 --> 00:20:16,077
Please, without trickery.

375
00:20:18,386 --> 00:20:19,087
I mean.

376
00:20:20,591 --> 00:20:21,378
Like this.

377
00:20:37,033 --> 00:20:37,918
Miraculous.

378
00:20:38,307 --> 00:20:40,014
The most remarkable
thing I've ever seen.

379
00:20:40,986 --> 00:20:43,472
Now. Now you all know what I can do.

380
00:20:45,254 --> 00:20:46,582
I can fool you too.

381
00:20:47,061 --> 00:20:49,214
So you have to take my
word for it that I won't.

382
00:20:50,554 --> 00:20:52,639
Now I will go into a
trance for you, if you like.

383
00:20:54,065 --> 00:20:57,334
The spirit controls
a sweet little child.

384
00:20:57,762 --> 00:20:58,901
Named 'Laughing-Eyes'.

385
00:21:00,299 --> 00:21:01,010
Wait.

386
00:21:01,810 --> 00:21:02,873
Don't speak.

387
00:21:05,209 --> 00:21:06,022
Don't.

388
00:21:06,606 --> 00:21:07,978
Don't say anything.

389
00:21:09,310 --> 00:21:10,863
There's a message coming.

390
00:21:11,694 --> 00:21:12,738
There is a message.

391
00:21:17,884 --> 00:21:18,536
No.

392
00:21:19,131 --> 00:21:20,552
No. Laughing-Eyes is gone.

393
00:21:21,937 --> 00:21:23,341
It is the unbelievers.

394
00:21:24,017 --> 00:21:25,587
Most of you don't believe.

395
00:21:26,133 --> 00:21:27,984
It's hard to get messages that way.

396
00:21:28,808 --> 00:21:29,574
I think.

397
00:21:30,120 --> 00:21:32,795
I think I might as well
go about my business.

398
00:21:33,378 --> 00:21:36,400
I thought she would when she found
out she was at Sir Roscoe's house.

399
00:21:37,125 --> 00:21:38,145
Did you now?

400
00:21:38,753 --> 00:21:41,437
Won't you please stay?
- I'm afraid I can't, ma'am.

401
00:21:41,935 --> 00:21:44,980
You see, I'm not just myself.
I'm not feeling just right.

402
00:21:45,318 --> 00:21:47,077
Madam La Grange,
under the circumstances ..

403
00:21:47,449 --> 00:21:48,407
I am sorry, sir.

404
00:21:48,785 --> 00:21:50,896
But I got to go home.
- I think it's a shame.

405
00:21:51,266 --> 00:21:52,970
I think she is quite right to go.

406
00:21:53,395 --> 00:21:55,842
Her sort of tricks aren't for
people of intelligence.

407
00:21:56,440 --> 00:21:57,201
Well.

408
00:21:58,602 --> 00:22:00,055
Won't you please stay?

409
00:22:00,886 --> 00:22:02,647
I must not, Miss.
- But won't you?

410
00:22:03,193 --> 00:22:05,143
As a very great favour to me?

411
00:22:09,333 --> 00:22:10,166
Please.

412
00:22:12,644 --> 00:22:13,459
Well, Miss.

413
00:22:14,295 --> 00:22:15,659
Since you ask it.

414
00:22:16,512 --> 00:22:17,435
I'll stay.

415
00:22:17,799 --> 00:22:18,757
Madam La Grange.

416
00:22:19,451 --> 00:22:22,771
I assure you I am very interested
in the outcome of this seance.

417
00:22:23,802 --> 00:22:26,560
I warn you I shall watch your
manifestations very closely.

418
00:22:27,015 --> 00:22:28,296
Do so, sir. I want you to.

419
00:22:28,873 --> 00:22:31,567
I am going to ask you to
submit to certain conditions.

420
00:22:32,298 --> 00:22:34,728
Anything at all, sir. Anything at all.

421
00:22:35,335 --> 00:22:37,776
To forestall any
assistance from outside.

422
00:22:38,532 --> 00:22:39,595
I want to suggest.

423
00:22:40,044 --> 00:22:43,020
That all the doors and windows
of this room be securely locked.

424
00:22:43,408 --> 00:22:44,023
Yes.

425
00:22:44,426 --> 00:22:46,309
And I suggest that we
search Madam La Grange.

426
00:22:46,649 --> 00:22:48,576
That is of course, if she is willing.

427
00:22:49,272 --> 00:22:50,063
Why not?

428
00:22:50,547 --> 00:22:52,594
There's no holes in my stockings.

429
00:22:55,013 --> 00:22:57,381
I suppose it will be very difficult
for you to get results ..

430
00:22:57,806 --> 00:22:59,328
If we're all so antagonistic.

431
00:23:01,681 --> 00:23:02,673
It's up to them.

432
00:23:03,815 --> 00:23:07,278
If there's any that wants to
communicate with anyone.

433
00:23:08,675 --> 00:23:09,915
Maybe they can reach us.

434
00:23:10,703 --> 00:23:11,692
I don't know.

435
00:23:12,519 --> 00:23:14,081
Sure, I don't understand you at all.

436
00:23:14,769 --> 00:23:15,934
I show you my tricks.

437
00:23:16,454 --> 00:23:19,090
Would I do that if I wanted to fool you?
I would not.

438
00:23:19,794 --> 00:23:21,820
Then why not give me
credit for being honest?

439
00:23:22,160 --> 00:23:24,231
I don't think any of
us doubt your honesty.

440
00:23:24,923 --> 00:23:26,232
They are just sceptical.

441
00:23:26,809 --> 00:23:27,841
Thank you, ma'am.

442
00:23:28,063 --> 00:23:31,173
I don't think we need submit
Madam La Grange to being searched.

443
00:23:31,536 --> 00:23:32,866
I'm sure I don't mind, ma'am.

444
00:23:33,604 --> 00:23:36,446
That is, if none of you fine
ladies will be shocked.

445
00:23:37,054 --> 00:23:39,307
Seeing plain, hand-sewn underwear.

446
00:23:40,533 --> 00:23:43,096
Then will you come with me?
I am sure we won't be shocked.

447
00:23:43,624 --> 00:23:46,432
I wear that kind myself.
- Do you now, ma'am?

448
00:23:46,877 --> 00:23:47,893
We shan't be long.

449
00:23:48,248 --> 00:23:48,962
Ma'am.

450
00:23:49,503 --> 00:23:51,717
Would you mind if all the ladies came?

451
00:23:52,500 --> 00:23:55,653
Then they'll all be sure I'm
not concealing anything.

452
00:24:00,024 --> 00:24:02,405
I really believe that woman
has a power of some sort.

453
00:24:02,925 --> 00:24:03,912
Look here, Wales.

454
00:24:04,135 --> 00:24:05,408
What are we supposed to do?

455
00:24:05,793 --> 00:24:07,498
Ask her a lot of silly questions?

456
00:24:09,340 --> 00:24:12,129
I am going to find out
who killed Spencer Lee.

457
00:24:13,172 --> 00:24:14,770
You are going to do what, Edward?

458
00:24:16,496 --> 00:24:18,419
I am going to try to communicate.

459
00:24:18,943 --> 00:24:21,331
With the spirit of Spencer Lee.

460
00:24:22,909 --> 00:24:25,664
So that's your reason for bringing
this woman here tonight?

461
00:24:26,113 --> 00:24:26,947
Precisely.

462
00:24:27,610 --> 00:24:29,217
Have you any objections, Sir Roscoe?

463
00:24:30,813 --> 00:24:31,404
No.

464
00:24:31,758 --> 00:24:34,599
Look here, Wales.
Spencer Lee was an out-and-out rotter.

465
00:24:35,097 --> 00:24:36,370
Brandon.
- It's the truth.

466
00:24:36,775 --> 00:24:38,755
His killing was good
riddance to bad rubbish.

467
00:24:39,101 --> 00:24:41,784
Wait. Spencer Lee was my friend.

468
00:24:42,805 --> 00:24:44,123
Gentlemen, I beg of you.

469
00:24:44,550 --> 00:24:46,654
You see, Mary.
It was quite a waste of time.

470
00:24:47,011 --> 00:24:47,883
Quite absurd.

471
00:24:48,946 --> 00:24:50,800
I am perfectly satisfied anyway.

472
00:24:51,300 --> 00:24:52,394
You should be.

473
00:24:52,797 --> 00:24:54,119
I am glad of that, Miss.

474
00:24:54,835 --> 00:24:58,415
Did you expect to find trap doors
and fake spirits up my sleeves?

475
00:24:59,256 --> 00:25:00,483
One can never tell.

476
00:25:01,087 --> 00:25:01,673
No.

477
00:25:02,383 --> 00:25:06,570
And suppose that mine is the
only trade there is any tricks in.

478
00:25:07,134 --> 00:25:07,852
May I?

479
00:25:08,925 --> 00:25:09,883
Thank you, Miss.

480
00:25:11,131 --> 00:25:13,497
Ma'am. Would you tell the gentlemen ..

481
00:25:13,913 --> 00:25:16,859
To put the chairs in a circle.
Then I'll be right along.

482
00:25:17,250 --> 00:25:19,547
I hope you forgive us
for being so sceptical.

483
00:25:22,369 --> 00:25:24,419
I hope she has some good
news to tell us anyway.

484
00:25:35,377 --> 00:25:38,302
At least we found out that she
had nothing concealed on her.

485
00:25:41,868 --> 00:25:43,047
Darling.
- Mother.

486
00:25:43,675 --> 00:25:44,651
I did not know.

487
00:25:45,284 --> 00:25:48,425
I wouldn't have come here
for anything in the world.

488
00:25:49,088 --> 00:25:49,903
I wouldn't.

489
00:25:50,379 --> 00:25:53,366
They just brought me here.
I didn't know where I was coming.

490
00:25:54,126 --> 00:25:55,084
Don't tell them.

491
00:25:55,767 --> 00:25:58,380
Don't make me shame you
before your fine friends.

492
00:25:59,092 --> 00:26:01,199
I'll get away as quick as I can.
- Mother.

493
00:26:02,241 --> 00:26:03,304
Don't say that.

494
00:26:04,075 --> 00:26:06,545
There is no shame, darling.
I am proud. Proud.

495
00:26:06,925 --> 00:26:08,749
Don't ever say that again.

496
00:26:10,107 --> 00:26:11,094
Alright, darling.

497
00:26:11,500 --> 00:26:12,675
Tell them if you must.

498
00:26:13,043 --> 00:26:14,934
But let me get away first.

499
00:26:15,660 --> 00:26:16,246
No.

500
00:26:16,708 --> 00:26:19,751
Now I must go or they'll think
there is something wrong.

501
00:26:20,223 --> 00:26:21,162
Come along.

502
00:26:21,732 --> 00:26:23,957
I do wish you would let me tell them.
- No.

503
00:26:37,853 --> 00:26:39,412
Yes, gentlemen. In a circle, I think.

504
00:26:39,845 --> 00:26:41,776
Sorry, Sir Roscoe, if you
feel that way about it.

505
00:26:42,130 --> 00:26:43,334
Not a matter of feeling.

506
00:26:43,955 --> 00:26:45,789
I'm just a little sceptical perhaps.

507
00:26:47,555 --> 00:26:48,809
On the table I think.

508
00:26:49,160 --> 00:26:50,897
You sit there, Howard?
- Yes. I sit here.

509
00:26:51,201 --> 00:26:53,056
One, two, three, four.

510
00:26:54,655 --> 00:26:56,146
Yes. I might want lights.

511
00:26:57,028 --> 00:26:57,766
Richard.

512
00:26:58,264 --> 00:27:01,362
If I call for lights, give them to me.
Don't wait for anything.

513
00:27:01,845 --> 00:27:03,290
Right, dad. I'll sit right there.

514
00:27:07,088 --> 00:27:09,412
I assure you she has
nothing up her sleeve.

515
00:27:10,104 --> 00:27:11,175
Well, well.

516
00:27:12,223 --> 00:27:14,174
I am glad you are satisfied.

517
00:27:15,370 --> 00:27:15,985
Yes.

518
00:27:16,706 --> 00:27:17,722
Yes. That's right.

519
00:27:18,659 --> 00:27:19,994
That's the way we want it.

520
