782
00:39:59,310 --> 00:40:00,613
I don't want any surprises.

783
00:40:01,654 --> 00:40:05,116
Did the messages come
for anyone but Mr Wales?

784
00:40:05,510 --> 00:40:06,955
No. The calls were all for Wales.

785
00:40:07,432 --> 00:40:08,501
He kept on saying:

786
00:40:09,091 --> 00:40:10,888
'Do you know who killed you'?

787
00:40:13,532 --> 00:40:14,797
Did she mention a name?

788
00:40:15,255 --> 00:40:15,841
No.

789
00:40:16,988 --> 00:40:18,338
She gave a long moan.

790
00:40:20,615 --> 00:40:22,262
Then Edward Wales continued to ask.

791
00:40:22,830 --> 00:40:23,740
He said:

792
00:40:24,256 --> 00:40:25,987
'Tell me who killed you.
I want the name'.

793
00:40:27,067 --> 00:40:29,933
Suddenly he gave out an agonised
scream and cried out that he was hurt.

794
00:40:32,372 --> 00:40:34,074
He was dead when we
turned on the lights.

795
00:40:34,343 --> 00:40:35,587
Matron is here, Inspector.

796
00:40:36,403 --> 00:40:37,113
Thanks.

797
00:40:39,586 --> 00:40:41,116
One more question, Sir Roscoe.

798
00:40:42,965 --> 00:40:46,418
Did you get the impression that if
Mr Wales had not been killed ..

799
00:40:46,944 --> 00:40:49,019
His question would have been answered?
- Yes.

800
00:40:50,628 --> 00:40:52,348
It was well established in your mind.

801
00:40:53,111 --> 00:40:56,253
That Wales was the only
person <i>able</i> to get a message.

802
00:40:56,636 --> 00:40:57,830
I'm positive.

803
00:40:58,827 --> 00:41:02,411
Then he was killed in order to
prevent his question being answered?

804
00:41:02,708 --> 00:41:04,351
That's the impression we got.
- Surely.

805
00:41:04,573 --> 00:41:07,371
That leads to the conclusion
that whoever killed Wales ..

806
00:41:08,253 --> 00:41:10,806
Knew who had killed Spencer Lee.

807
00:41:14,861 --> 00:41:15,558
Well.

808
00:41:16,822 --> 00:41:20,220
There is a police matron in the other
room who will search the ladies.

809
00:41:20,857 --> 00:41:22,573
Grimshaw, the men. One at a time.

810
00:41:23,698 --> 00:41:26,065
It makes no difference to
me in what order they go.

811
00:41:26,529 --> 00:41:27,773
I have nothing to conceal.

812
00:41:28,536 --> 00:41:31,168
I'd rather you waited a few
minutes, Madam La Grange.

813
00:41:31,539 --> 00:41:33,035
I am quite ready.
- So am I.

814
00:41:33,428 --> 00:41:34,501
Thank you very much.

815
00:41:35,072 --> 00:41:36,661
You need not sit there anymore.

816
00:41:37,009 --> 00:41:38,211
Unless you wish.

817
00:41:44,486 --> 00:41:45,215
Richard.

818
00:41:45,874 --> 00:41:47,106
Madam La Grange.

819
00:41:47,616 --> 00:41:48,240
Sir?

820
00:41:49,668 --> 00:41:51,464
There is a question I wish to ask.

821
00:41:52,355 --> 00:41:53,456
Anything at all, sir.

822
00:41:54,049 --> 00:41:57,528
When Mr Wales asked you for the
name, why didn't you answer?

823
00:41:59,119 --> 00:42:00,135
I don't know, sir.

824
00:42:00,812 --> 00:42:01,828
I was in a trance.

825
00:42:03,411 --> 00:42:05,057
Then you did not hear the question?

826
00:42:05,487 --> 00:42:07,491
How could I?
- I didn't ask you that.

827
00:42:08,637 --> 00:42:10,225
I asked you why you didn't answer him.

828
00:42:11,046 --> 00:42:13,340
Why did you not carry out
your part of the bargain?

829
00:42:13,781 --> 00:42:15,054
I don't know what you mean.

830
00:42:15,543 --> 00:42:18,036
My words are perfectly plain.

831
00:42:18,790 --> 00:42:20,839
Why didn't you carry out
your part of the bargain?

832
00:42:21,231 --> 00:42:24,083
There wasn't any bargain.
- Your whole seance was a fake.

833
00:42:26,334 --> 00:42:29,311
It was not only planned but rehearsed.
Between you and Wales.

834
00:42:30,621 --> 00:42:32,547
He saw that a woman
had killed his friend.

835
00:42:32,769 --> 00:42:36,047
And he told you about it and asked
your help to discover the murderer.

836
00:42:36,988 --> 00:42:39,086
I don't know what you're
talking about at all.

837
00:42:42,003 --> 00:42:42,895
Perhaps this.

838
00:42:43,475 --> 00:42:44,807
Will refresh your memory.

839
00:42:48,731 --> 00:42:49,775
'What do you want'?

840
00:42:50,563 --> 00:42:51,264
Answer:

841
00:42:52,024 --> 00:42:53,469
'Don't forget the swimming pool'.

842
00:42:54,184 --> 00:42:56,115
'Don't ever forget the swimming pool'.

843
00:42:57,336 --> 00:42:57,980
Then.

844
00:42:58,918 --> 00:43:01,851
'Do you mean the time he went
in after me when I was drowning'?

845
00:43:05,239 --> 00:43:06,074
Then later.

846
00:43:06,527 --> 00:43:08,544
'Spencer Lee says he can't rest'.

847
00:43:09,292 --> 00:43:11,221
And so on and so on down to ..

848
00:43:12,357 --> 00:43:14,483
'Do you know who killed you'?

849
00:43:17,008 --> 00:43:19,408
The answer to that
would have been: 'Yes'.

850
00:43:20,707 --> 00:43:21,706
What did she say?

851
00:43:22,277 --> 00:43:23,926
She did not answer that question.

852
00:43:25,685 --> 00:43:26,786
The next question is.

853
00:43:28,508 --> 00:43:29,748
Can you tell the name?

854
00:43:31,826 --> 00:43:32,551
Then.

855
00:43:33,340 --> 00:43:35,821
He was to have told a woman's name.

856
00:43:37,039 --> 00:43:38,341
Just the first name.

857
00:43:39,461 --> 00:43:41,521
Sir Roscoe, what did she
reply to that question?

858
00:43:42,024 --> 00:43:43,399
She moaned and cried.

859
00:43:44,165 --> 00:43:45,974
'Keep on asking. Keep on asking'.

860
00:43:47,169 --> 00:43:48,727
Why didn't you do as you agreed?

861
00:43:49,585 --> 00:43:51,707
I don't know what you're
talking about at all.

862
00:43:53,038 --> 00:43:53,825
You don't?

863
00:43:56,683 --> 00:43:57,890
Mr Wales. Sure he was.

864
00:43:58,412 --> 00:44:01,753
That a woman killed Spencer Lee and
he was sure that he found that woman.

865
00:44:02,899 --> 00:44:04,741
But he dared not accuse her.

866
00:44:05,845 --> 00:44:07,570
Or even tell me her name.

867
00:44:08,706 --> 00:44:11,199
But he knew she would be here tonight.

868
00:44:12,715 --> 00:44:14,861
He thought he could play
on her superstitious fears.

869
00:44:15,394 --> 00:44:18,267
That when her name seemingly came
from the spirit of the dead man.

870
00:44:18,719 --> 00:44:20,030
She would confess.

871
00:44:21,179 --> 00:44:22,877
He told Madam La Grange the name.

872
00:44:23,305 --> 00:44:24,464
You agreed to all this.

873
00:44:24,862 --> 00:44:26,221
Why didn't you speak the name?

874
00:44:27,008 --> 00:44:28,620
I don't know anything about it.

875
00:44:31,125 --> 00:44:32,784
He must have forgotten to tell it.

876
00:44:33,410 --> 00:44:34,697
No. He didn't.

877
00:44:35,368 --> 00:44:36,498
There wasn't any name.

878
00:44:37,071 --> 00:44:40,208
He didn't tell me any name.
- You came here for that purpose.

879
00:44:40,894 --> 00:44:42,227
And after you got here.

880
00:44:43,129 --> 00:44:44,682
Something happened.

881
00:44:45,650 --> 00:44:47,748
To make you change your plan.

882
00:44:49,566 --> 00:44:52,963
Something unexpected happened.

883
00:44:56,085 --> 00:44:59,123
Something unexpected happened.

884
00:45:00,213 --> 00:45:00,869
Now.

885
00:45:01,589 --> 00:45:02,798
What was it?

886
00:45:03,270 --> 00:45:04,896
What was it?
- That is over.

887
00:45:05,860 --> 00:45:07,325
Mrs Eastwood.

888
00:45:08,949 --> 00:45:10,564
What did you say was your first name?

889
00:45:11,187 --> 00:45:12,440
Mary.
- Mary.

890
00:45:13,553 --> 00:45:15,065
And yours?
- Grace.

891
00:45:16,399 --> 00:45:18,579
Sir Roscoe, your wife's given name?
- Alice.

892
00:45:18,973 --> 00:45:19,645
Alice.

893
00:45:21,846 --> 00:45:22,945
Mrs Trent.

894
00:45:24,544 --> 00:45:25,306
Helen.

895
00:45:43,290 --> 00:45:45,049
And yours, Miss O'Neill?

896
00:45:45,667 --> 00:45:46,720
Helen.
- Helen?

897
00:45:47,116 --> 00:45:49,800
You see, I was christened Helen
but my friends call me 'Nellie'.

898
00:45:50,863 --> 00:45:51,857
I see.

899
00:45:54,612 --> 00:45:55,284
Helen.

900
00:45:58,087 --> 00:45:58,793
Helen.

901
00:46:00,312 --> 00:46:02,957
So there are two .. Helens.

902
00:46:05,990 --> 00:46:06,605
Two.

903
00:46:07,892 --> 00:46:08,593
Helens.

904
00:46:11,246 --> 00:46:13,947
Sir Roscoe.
When Madam La Grange first came tonight.

905
00:46:14,288 --> 00:46:16,902
Did she show any surprise at
seeing any of the people here?

906
00:46:17,267 --> 00:46:18,539
I was not in the room.

907
00:46:19,073 --> 00:46:21,636
I was in the library with
Miss O'Neill and my son.

908
00:46:24,372 --> 00:46:27,239
Then Miss O'Neill was not in
the room when she arrived?

909
00:46:38,260 --> 00:46:40,718
So there were <i>two</i> Helens.

910
00:46:44,771 --> 00:46:48,006
Everything was going along smoothly
until Miss O'Neill came in.

911
00:46:49,270 --> 00:46:50,721
The extra Helen.

912
00:46:52,634 --> 00:46:53,799
Rosalie La Grange.

913
00:46:55,289 --> 00:46:57,334
What is that girl to you?

914
00:46:58,332 --> 00:46:59,061
Nothing.

915
00:46:59,569 --> 00:47:01,318
Nothing at all.
- Nothing at all?

916
00:47:01,898 --> 00:47:04,564
Then why did you try to deceive
me as to where she sat?

917
00:47:05,434 --> 00:47:08,996
Why did you place her so that I wouldn't
know she was sitting next to Mr Wales ..

918
00:47:09,553 --> 00:47:10,700
When he was stabbed?

919
00:47:11,199 --> 00:47:12,358
It was just a mistake.

920
00:47:12,884 --> 00:47:15,295
I didn't ask her to do it.
- I'm afraid that won't do.

921
00:47:16,223 --> 00:47:18,771
You spoke of your plans and
the name you were to speak ..

922
00:47:19,308 --> 00:47:20,236
Was 'Helen'.

923
00:47:22,238 --> 00:47:23,717
What is the use of lying to me?

924
00:47:25,309 --> 00:47:27,141
You tried your best to shield this girl.

925
00:47:27,581 --> 00:47:29,131
And I want to know why.

926
00:47:30,317 --> 00:47:31,843
I didn't ask her to do it.

927
00:47:33,480 --> 00:47:35,732
I never heard of the young
lady before in all my life.

928
00:47:36,060 --> 00:47:37,747
What is that girl to you?
- Nothing.

929
00:47:38,298 --> 00:47:39,543
Nothing at all.

930
00:47:40,103 --> 00:47:42,084
You old harridan ..
- Leave my mother alone.

931
00:47:42,458 --> 00:47:43,416
Leave her alone.

932
00:47:46,866 --> 00:47:48,046
I thought perhaps.

933
00:47:48,717 --> 00:47:50,087
I would get it that way.

934
00:47:50,649 --> 00:47:52,130
There, dear. It's alright.

935
00:47:53,215 --> 00:47:54,550
Of course it is alright.

936
00:47:55,126 --> 00:47:57,026
We'll have the fingerprints and ..

937
00:47:57,471 --> 00:47:59,884
If you think for one moment ..
- Richard, my boy. Please.

938
00:48:00,624 --> 00:48:01,811
Think.
- Think nothing.

939
00:48:02,122 --> 00:48:04,616
Young man .. don't be foolish.

940
00:48:06,245 --> 00:48:07,060
I am sorry.

941
00:48:08,471 --> 00:48:10,371
But it is too clear.

942
00:48:10,863 --> 00:48:11,577
Clear?

943
00:48:12,073 --> 00:48:13,656
Lordy be, how could it be clear?

944
00:48:15,888 --> 00:48:18,400
You will never accuse my
little girl of a thing like that.

945
00:48:18,801 --> 00:48:20,004
She was next to him.

946
00:48:20,522 --> 00:48:23,462
She had only to free one hand,
strike, and take his hand again.

947
00:48:23,873 --> 00:48:24,491
No.

948
00:48:24,812 --> 00:48:27,237
There was something else she had
to do before she could do that.

949
00:48:27,951 --> 00:48:29,587
She had to have murder in her heart.

950
00:48:30,924 --> 00:48:31,768
Look at her.

951
00:48:32,145 --> 00:48:34,438
Look at the eyes of her.
At the face of her.

952
00:48:35,249 --> 00:48:36,507
Is a murderer there?

953
00:48:37,253 --> 00:48:39,509
Man. Haven't you got eyes in your head?

954
00:48:39,883 --> 00:48:41,843
No knife on them, Inspector.
- I know where it is.

955
00:48:42,167 --> 00:48:44,346
Tell the matron she will
find the knife on this girl.

956
00:48:44,732 --> 00:48:45,681
Take her away.

957
00:48:46,581 --> 00:48:47,368
Inspector.

958
00:48:47,945 --> 00:48:50,392
Don't do it.
I'll tell you anything you like.

959
00:48:50,849 --> 00:48:52,762
Only keep your hands off my little girl.

960
00:48:53,265 --> 00:48:54,803
I did come here like you said.

961
00:48:55,365 --> 00:48:58,158
And when I seen my own
child I lost my head.

962
00:48:59,099 --> 00:49:01,162
I'm a silly old woman
that ain't got any sense.

963
00:49:01,982 --> 00:49:03,281
I tried to save her.

964
00:49:03,811 --> 00:49:05,473
And I've only made matters worse.

965
00:49:06,129 --> 00:49:07,393
But you've looked at her.

966
00:49:07,970 --> 00:49:10,254
You can't think she'd
do a thing like that?

967
00:49:10,639 --> 00:49:11,254
Yes.

968
00:49:12,129 --> 00:49:14,028
Then, Inspector. You are a fool.

969
00:49:14,473 --> 00:49:16,817
And god helping me, I'll prove it.

970
00:49:32,949 --> 00:49:33,793
No. I can't.

971
00:49:34,109 --> 00:49:36,310
I don't know why you ever allowed
this woman to come here.

972
00:49:43,858 --> 00:49:45,438
Is he still there, Howard?
- Yes.

973
00:49:46,237 --> 00:49:49,316
And I hope he takes root there.
I hope he grows like a berry tree.

974
00:49:49,644 --> 00:49:50,951
It's a beastly outrage.

975
00:49:51,308 --> 00:49:54,378
Here we are, searched and held
prisoners like common criminals.

976
00:49:55,770 --> 00:49:56,471
Father.

977
00:49:56,909 --> 00:50:00,138
They searched and found nothing. Can you
insist they release her from that room?

978
00:50:00,554 --> 00:50:02,285
I'll see what I can do, Richard.
- Please.

979
00:50:02,666 --> 00:50:04,059
Richard, where is her mother?

980
00:50:04,423 --> 00:50:08,380
I don't know. They only told me to come
in here and wait until I was wanted.

981
00:50:09,177 --> 00:50:09,878
Oh god.

982
00:50:11,028 --> 00:50:12,320
Show me the way.

983
00:50:14,416 --> 00:50:16,769
Sure, I've been a faker all my life.

984
00:50:18,046 --> 00:50:19,351
I have tricked them.

985
00:50:19,784 --> 00:50:20,928
And fooled them.

986
00:50:22,582 --> 00:50:23,397
But honest.

987
00:50:24,598 --> 00:50:27,857
I never knowingly done harm to anyone.

988
00:50:30,538 --> 00:50:32,355
And there is a power.

989
00:50:34,088 --> 00:50:35,835
It came to me before.

990
00:50:37,966 --> 00:50:38,806
Oh god.

991
00:50:40,322 --> 00:50:41,585
Give it to me again.

992
00:50:44,306 --> 00:50:45,376
It is fate.

993
00:50:47,380 --> 00:50:48,415
My little girl.

994
00:50:50,905 --> 00:50:51,999
For the sake.

995
00:50:53,261 --> 00:50:54,749
For the sake of your son.

996
00:50:57,858 --> 00:50:58,702
Amen.

997
00:51:32,639 --> 00:51:36,034
I quite understand but is it necessary
to keep her locked in that room?

998
00:51:39,386 --> 00:51:41,165
Who turned off those other lights?

999
00:51:41,950 --> 00:51:43,649
I did, sir.
- Why?

1000
00:51:44,680 --> 00:51:45,669
Well, sir.

1001
00:51:46,333 --> 00:51:47,589
I was praying.

1002
00:51:48,455 --> 00:51:49,992
Praying? What for?

1003
00:51:51,864 --> 00:51:52,622
Guidance.

1004
00:51:53,050 --> 00:51:54,152
I hope you get it.

1005
00:51:54,749 --> 00:51:55,610
I will, sir.

1006
00:51:56,028 --> 00:51:57,972
Take her to the matron
and have her searched.

1007
00:51:58,452 --> 00:51:59,824
Unless of course.

1008
00:52:00,787 --> 00:52:02,669
You want to give up the knife now.

1009
00:52:03,430 --> 00:52:04,360
I got no knife.

1010
00:52:04,956 --> 00:52:06,983
And I've been searched once.
- Exactly.

1011
00:52:07,721 --> 00:52:10,240
But then you were allowed
to come into this room.

1012
00:52:11,738 --> 00:52:13,743
We're rather anxious to
know what you found ..

1013
00:52:14,609 --> 00:52:15,812
While you were in here.

1014
00:52:17,579 --> 00:52:19,089
A feeling of comfort, sir.

1015
00:52:20,272 --> 00:52:21,770
A feeling that the innocent ..

1016
00:52:22,391 --> 00:52:23,912
Had come to no harm.

1017
00:52:25,258 --> 00:52:26,421
Take her to the matron.

1018
00:52:28,856 --> 00:52:29,957
Take her out of here.

1019
00:52:31,186 --> 00:52:32,287
I'm going.

1020
00:52:36,084 --> 00:52:38,143
You wanted me?
- Yes. Sit down.

1021
00:52:38,591 --> 00:52:40,057
My dear girl.
- Sir Roscoe.

1022
00:52:40,723 --> 00:52:42,082
If you caution her in any way.

1023
00:52:42,461 --> 00:52:44,217
You're interfering
in this investigation.

1024
00:52:44,568 --> 00:52:46,099
I beg your pardon, Inspector.

1025
00:52:47,697 --> 00:52:50,041
I say, Ellis. What happened
here at the window?

1026
00:52:50,631 --> 00:52:53,538
The old woman turned the blind
and stood gazing outside.

1027
00:52:53,947 --> 00:52:56,050
Did she throw anything out the window?
- No, Inspector.

1028
00:52:57,532 --> 00:52:59,619
Now, young woman.
Let's see what you have to say.

1029
00:52:59,995 --> 00:53:02,430
I've already told you there
is nothing that I can say.

1030
00:53:02,857 --> 00:53:04,812
Well, You'd better make
up your mind to talk.

1031
00:53:05,245 --> 00:53:06,826
Now. Out with the truth.

1032
00:53:07,342 --> 00:53:08,644
She will 'out' with nothing.

1033
00:53:10,544 --> 00:53:14,291
You say you got the fingerprints of the
girl that was in Spencer Lee's room.

1034
00:53:14,901 --> 00:53:16,718
And you got my Nellie's fingerprints.

1035
00:53:17,479 --> 00:53:19,235
Why don't you compare them?
- Mother.

1036
00:53:19,811 --> 00:53:21,558
What were you going to say?
- Nothing.

1037
00:53:21,979 --> 00:53:22,859
Inspector.

1038
00:53:23,340 --> 00:53:26,057
The fingerprints compare perfectly.
- That is a lie.

1039
00:53:26,465 --> 00:53:28,654
Sir Roscoe, we have taken this
young woman's fingerprints.

1040
00:53:29,654 --> 00:53:31,897
And there is the cup which we
took from Spencer Lee's room.

1041
00:53:33,240 --> 00:53:35,586
Her fingerprints are on that cup.

1042
00:53:35,937 --> 00:53:37,257
I never touched a cup.

1043
00:53:38,573 --> 00:53:39,437
Thanks.

1044
00:53:41,441 --> 00:53:42,724
I know that fact.

1045
00:53:43,229 --> 00:53:44,872
Then you said that just to trap her?

1046
00:53:45,242 --> 00:53:47,444
There are no fingerprints on the cup.

1047
00:53:48,509 --> 00:53:50,010
We merely wanted her admission.

1048
00:53:50,736 --> 00:53:51,891
She was there.

1049
00:53:56,546 --> 00:53:57,247
Nellie.

1050
00:53:58,142 --> 00:53:58,957
Look at me.

1051
00:54:01,130 --> 00:54:02,387
Look at your old mother.

1052
00:54:03,900 --> 00:54:04,601
Mother.

1053
00:54:06,862 --> 00:54:08,255
What if she did go there?

1054
00:54:08,828 --> 00:54:10,158
She had a good reason for it.

1055
00:54:11,488 --> 00:54:13,319
What did you go for, darling?

1056
00:54:14,163 --> 00:54:15,449
I can't tell you.

1057
00:54:16,693 --> 00:54:18,250
Nellie, dear. You must tell me.

1058
00:54:20,619 --> 00:54:21,672
Dear, listen.

1059
00:54:22,259 --> 00:54:23,503
You know that I trust you.

1060
00:54:24,041 --> 00:54:25,400
You know that we all love you.

1061
00:54:26,243 --> 00:54:27,756
Now explain to him, dear.

1062
00:54:28,341 --> 00:54:28,985
Well?

1063
00:54:29,913 --> 00:54:30,763
I'm waiting.

1064
00:54:31,083 --> 00:54:32,184
I didn't do anything.

1065
00:54:32,502 --> 00:54:33,816
I didn't do anything.

1066
00:54:34,340 --> 00:54:36,815
Yes, my dear. We know that.
But why did you go?

1067
00:54:37,214 --> 00:54:38,935
Did you know Spencer Lee?

1068
00:54:39,310 --> 00:54:40,786
Of course she didn't, father.

1069
00:54:41,126 --> 00:54:42,608
Why doesn't she speak for herself?

1070
00:54:42,919 --> 00:54:44,192
Because I'll speak for her.

1071
00:54:44,652 --> 00:54:46,864
My dear, can't you answer
even that question?

1072
00:54:47,933 --> 00:54:49,778
Don't you see what they'll
think if you don't?

1073
00:54:50,136 --> 00:54:51,393
Nellie, you must tell me.

1074
00:54:52,045 --> 00:54:52,746
Nellie.

1075
00:54:53,325 --> 00:54:55,108
You're shielding someone.
- No, no.

1076
00:54:55,528 --> 00:54:57,338
That's the first lie you ever told me.

1077
00:54:58,130 --> 00:54:59,936
I want to know who you are shielding.

1078
00:55:00,614 --> 00:55:02,361
Tell me who it is.
- Please dear.

1079
00:55:03,157 --> 00:55:05,195
You're her sweetheart. Make her tell.

1080
00:55:05,512 --> 00:55:08,004
Dear, you must. You must.
- Richard, I can't.

1081
00:55:09,485 --> 00:55:11,731
Even if you are protecting someone else.

1082
00:55:12,296 --> 00:55:13,692
I think you ought to tell us.

1083
00:55:14,466 --> 00:55:15,598
Break her word, is it?

1084
00:55:16,176 --> 00:55:17,106
She should not.

1085
00:55:17,720 --> 00:55:20,192
There never was an O'Neill
yet that was an informer.

1086
00:55:22,868 --> 00:55:24,098
She needn't tell.

1087
00:55:24,825 --> 00:55:26,344
I know it myself now.

1088
00:55:27,146 --> 00:55:28,669
It is blind, I've been.

1089
00:55:31,037 --> 00:55:31,652
You.

1090
00:55:44,739 --> 00:55:47,531
You're the one who found
out there was two Helens.

1091
00:55:48,281 --> 00:55:50,321
'The extra Helen', says you.

1092
00:55:51,163 --> 00:55:53,165
Well, send for the other Helen.

1093
00:55:53,633 --> 00:55:54,963
And ask her.
- Mother, stop.

1094
00:55:55,345 --> 00:55:56,332
Stop? I will not.

1095
00:55:56,648 --> 00:55:57,520
Wait, please.

1096
00:55:58,641 --> 00:55:59,857
Did my daughter send you?

1097
00:56:00,493 --> 00:56:02,856
Because if she did we
can't accept that sacrifice.

1098
00:56:04,139 --> 00:56:05,647
I want to know the truth.

1099
00:56:06,987 --> 00:56:08,458
Did my daughter send you?

1100
00:56:09,859 --> 00:56:11,375
Did you go for my daughter?

1101
00:56:12,281 --> 00:56:12,896
Yes.

1102
00:56:13,266 --> 00:56:14,052
I knew it.

1103
00:56:14,557 --> 00:56:15,974
My daughter sent you?

1104
00:56:17,232 --> 00:56:18,159
What for?

1105
00:56:18,746 --> 00:56:20,261
Some letters.
- Why didn't she go?

1106
00:56:20,578 --> 00:56:22,151
She was afraid.
- Go on.

1107
00:56:22,750 --> 00:56:24,080
Tell him, dear. It's alright.

1108
00:56:24,588 --> 00:56:25,975
I don't know what to say.

1109
00:56:26,449 --> 00:56:27,618
Why not tell the truth?

1110
00:56:28,369 --> 00:56:30,154
Tell the inspector what happened.

1111
00:56:32,356 --> 00:56:33,509
Nothing happened.

1112
00:56:35,556 --> 00:56:40,300
They were silly letters Helen wrote to
Mr Lee before she married Mr Trent.

1113
00:56:42,475 --> 00:56:43,204
You see.

1114
00:56:43,520 --> 00:56:46,637
Mr Lee knew that Mr Trent
was terribly jealous, and ..

1115
00:56:47,494 --> 00:56:50,571
He threatened to send the letters to
him if Helen didn't come to his room.

1116
00:56:52,493 --> 00:56:55,308
Helen confided in me
and I went to Mr Lee.

1117
00:56:56,550 --> 00:56:58,747
He said that he loved
Helen and was desperate.

1118
00:56:59,696 --> 00:57:01,490
It seemed like a funny kind of love.

1119
00:57:02,068 --> 00:57:03,341
But I didn't tell him that.

1120
00:57:03,944 --> 00:57:05,420
Then he gave me the letters.

1121
00:57:05,929 --> 00:57:07,970
Was it before or after
Mr Lee ordered tea?

1122
00:57:08,322 --> 00:57:09,128
After.

1123
00:57:09,526 --> 00:57:11,227
I compliment this young lady.

1124
00:57:12,413 --> 00:57:13,464
That was ..

1125
00:57:14,133 --> 00:57:15,595
Beautifully done.

1126
00:57:16,252 --> 00:57:18,011
Grimshaw, get Miss Trent.
- Yes, Inspector.

1127
00:57:18,388 --> 00:57:19,833
You don't believe?
- Not a word.

1128
00:57:20,217 --> 00:57:21,335
Not one word.

1129
00:57:21,959 --> 00:57:23,445
She wasn't protecting your sister.

1130
00:57:23,896 --> 00:57:25,438
She was protecting herself.

1131
00:57:26,716 --> 00:57:28,230
She went for the letters of course.

1132
00:57:28,571 --> 00:57:30,623
But the tea was served
before she asked for them.

1133
00:57:30,988 --> 00:57:32,796
Not afterwards.
- How do you know that?

1134
00:57:33,169 --> 00:57:36,016
The butler would not serve tea
to a man she had just killed.

1135
00:57:36,460 --> 00:57:37,476
You ..
- Richard.

1136
00:57:37,729 --> 00:57:38,918
She was engaged to him.

1137
00:57:39,866 --> 00:57:42,056
He had compromising letters
she had written to him.

1138
00:57:42,543 --> 00:57:44,057
So she went to get them.

1139
00:57:44,783 --> 00:57:47,022
Then, when he wouldn't give them to her.

1140
00:57:47,478 --> 00:57:48,443
She killed him.

1141
00:57:49,207 --> 00:57:50,044
Mrs Trent.

1142
00:57:50,266 --> 00:57:51,220
Yes, Inspector?

1143
00:57:51,825 --> 00:57:55,707
Did you ask this girl to go to Mr Lee's
rooms to get letters you wrote to him?

1144
00:57:56,095 --> 00:57:57,112
Did she what?

1145
00:57:57,511 --> 00:57:59,041
Did you, Mrs Trent?

1146
00:58:00,458 --> 00:58:01,551
Certainly not.

1147
00:58:02,378 --> 00:58:03,724
Helen, I ..
- Keep still.

1148
00:58:05,534 --> 00:58:08,007
Are you sure?
- Of course she is sure.

1149
00:58:08,804 --> 00:58:10,149
Please answer my question.

1150
00:58:11,716 --> 00:58:13,994
I never wrote a letter to
Spencer Lee in my life.

1151
00:58:15,626 --> 00:58:18,056
I don't know what she told you.
- Never mind what she told me.

1152
00:58:18,385 --> 00:58:20,041
I want to be very sure of this.

1153
00:58:21,367 --> 00:58:23,918
Did you ask this girl to
go to Spencer Lee's room?

1154
00:58:24,482 --> 00:58:25,121
No.

1155
00:58:25,976 --> 00:58:27,544
She had no letters of yours?
- No.

1156
00:58:27,934 --> 00:58:29,486
Nellie didn't know Lee, Helen.

1157
00:58:29,708 --> 00:58:31,879
And you did.
- How about that, Mrs Trent?

1158
00:58:33,182 --> 00:58:34,926
I think Nellie knew Spencer Lee.

1159
00:58:36,159 --> 00:58:37,587
I hadn't seen him for months.

1160
00:58:38,327 --> 00:58:39,797
He used to come here a good deal.

1161
00:58:40,693 --> 00:58:41,823
He wanted to marry me.

1162
00:58:42,801 --> 00:58:43,931
But I didn't like him.

1163
00:58:45,075 --> 00:58:47,633
And I certainly never wrote
him letters of any sort.

1164
00:58:48,443 --> 00:58:50,056
Thank you, Mrs Trent.

1165
00:58:51,970 --> 00:58:53,779
That is all I want to know.

1166
00:58:54,184 --> 00:58:56,552
Helen, you're lying to save yourself.
You must tell the truth.

1167
00:58:56,806 --> 00:58:58,279
She tells the truth.
- She's not.

1168
00:58:58,572 --> 00:58:59,737
Richard, wait.

1169
00:59:00,641 --> 00:59:01,342
Please.

1170
00:59:02,960 --> 00:59:04,098
I'm sorry, Richard.

1171
00:59:04,427 --> 00:59:06,671
Father, you don't think ..
- No, dear. I don't.

1172
00:59:08,101 --> 00:59:10,662
Inspector, do you need us anymore?
- Not anymore.

1173
00:59:11,237 --> 00:59:12,212
Thank you.

1174
00:59:14,831 --> 00:59:15,589
Grimshaw.

1175
00:59:16,299 --> 00:59:17,750
Take her to police headquarters.

1176
00:59:18,126 --> 00:59:19,547
No. Not my Nellie.

1177
00:59:20,168 --> 00:59:20,955
Inspector.

1178
00:59:21,277 --> 00:59:22,693
I wouldn't do that if I was you.

1179
00:59:23,320 --> 00:59:25,532
I know who done it.
- You know? Who was it?

1180
00:59:26,019 --> 00:59:28,544
I can't tell you yet.
But I will, I will.

1181
00:59:29,272 --> 00:59:30,312
Give me a chance.

1182
00:59:30,653 --> 00:59:31,674
Give me time.

1183
00:59:32,132 --> 00:59:33,095
Give me an hour.

1184
00:59:33,835 --> 00:59:35,674
Keep them all here in the house.

1185
00:59:36,202 --> 00:59:37,218
An hour more.

1186
00:59:40,715 --> 00:59:41,749
I'll give you.

1187
00:59:42,758 --> 00:59:43,723
Ten minutes.

1188
00:59:44,560 --> 00:59:45,404
Ten minutes?

1189
00:59:48,433 --> 00:59:49,289
Bless me.

1190
00:59:49,748 --> 00:59:51,638
No, darling. Not now. Go away.

1191
00:59:52,922 --> 00:59:55,388
Inspector, won't you take them all away?

1192
00:59:56,386 --> 00:59:57,574
Please.
- Alright.

1193
00:59:58,165 --> 00:59:59,432
Go away please.
- Come.

1194
01:00:01,158 --> 01:00:02,037
Ten minutes.

1195
01:00:04,555 --> 01:00:05,456
What can I do?

1196
01:00:06,396 --> 01:00:07,394
What can I do?

1197
01:00:11,590 --> 01:00:13,144
I said I knew who done it.

1198
01:00:13,965 --> 01:00:14,809
But I don't.

1199
01:00:17,359 --> 01:00:18,690
Sure, Laughing-Eyes.

1200
01:00:20,196 --> 01:00:21,846
You're no good to me now.

1201
01:00:23,337 --> 01:00:24,711
We've faked all our lives.

1202
01:00:26,208 --> 01:00:28,176
Now, when I want the real thing.

1203
01:00:30,389 --> 01:00:31,982
I get nothing at all.

1204
01:00:35,015 --> 01:00:36,601
If only I could get ..

1205
01:00:37,400 --> 01:00:38,738
A real message.

1206
01:00:41,416 --> 01:00:42,446
Laughing-Eyes.

1207
01:00:44,275 --> 01:00:45,273
Laughing-Eyes.

1208
01:00:46,994 --> 01:00:49,095
Are you going to let me be beaten?

1209
01:00:50,227 --> 01:00:51,362
By a scheming ..

1210
01:00:52,184 --> 01:00:54,145
Cold-hearted murderer?

1211
01:00:54,865 --> 01:00:56,426
[ Two raps. ]

1212
01:01:04,716 --> 01:01:05,958
I didn't do that.

1213
01:01:10,350 --> 01:01:11,519
I didn't do that.

1214
01:01:14,009 --> 01:01:14,931
It's come.

1215
01:01:16,492 --> 01:01:18,418
After all these years.

1216
01:01:19,877 --> 01:01:21,146
A real message.

1217
01:01:23,183 --> 01:01:24,444
I will take it.

1218
01:01:25,419 --> 01:01:26,232
Believing.

1219
01:01:26,769 --> 01:01:27,930
And trusting.

1220
01:01:28,959 --> 01:01:30,588
The time to be sure.

1221
01:01:38,291 --> 01:01:39,453
Glory be.

1222
01:01:41,015 --> 01:01:41,951
The knife.

1223
01:01:46,561 --> 01:01:47,564
I knocked twice.

1224
01:01:47,948 --> 01:01:49,131
But you didn't hear me.

1225
01:01:50,968 --> 01:01:52,186
I heard you.

1226
01:01:55,231 --> 01:01:56,504
That was a message.

1227
01:01:57,610 --> 01:01:58,885
Just the same.

1228
01:02:03,497 --> 01:02:04,410
Inspector.

1229
01:02:05,114 --> 01:02:06,612
I got to speak to you alone.

1230
01:02:07,282 --> 01:02:08,066
I got to.

1231
01:02:09,415 --> 01:02:10,746
You must let me.

1232
01:02:12,133 --> 01:02:13,434
You've got to let me.

1233
01:02:14,651 --> 01:02:15,612
Very well.

1234
01:02:20,847 --> 01:02:22,455
The constable outside is ordered ..

1235
01:02:23,265 --> 01:02:25,572
To arrest anyone leaving this house.

1236
01:02:27,500 --> 01:02:30,408
What did mother mean, Richard?
What did she mean, 'a message'?

1237
01:02:31,578 --> 01:02:32,716
I don't know, dear.

1238
01:02:33,388 --> 01:02:34,089
Please.

1239
01:02:34,729 --> 01:02:35,893
Please, Inspector.

1240
01:02:36,577 --> 01:02:37,676
Do as I ask.

1241
01:02:39,125 --> 01:02:40,112
Give me a chance.

1242
01:02:41,528 --> 01:02:43,193
Then, if it does work.

1243
01:02:43,582 --> 01:02:45,392
You can take my Nellie and lock her up.

1244
01:02:46,876 --> 01:02:47,917
Please, Inspector.

1245
01:02:48,814 --> 01:02:50,293
I know my Nellie will do it.

1246
01:02:51,028 --> 01:02:52,799
Let's see if the other one will.

1247
01:02:53,461 --> 01:02:55,257
What you are asking me to let you do ..

1248
01:02:55,976 --> 01:02:57,019
Is insanity.

1249
01:02:58,139 --> 01:02:59,274
It is unheard of.

1250
01:03:00,296 --> 01:03:01,624
Inspector, please.

1251
01:03:02,499 --> 01:03:03,755
Don't you see?

1252
01:03:04,222 --> 01:03:05,237
I am drowning.

1253
01:03:05,971 --> 01:03:07,916
And I'm snatching at the last straw.

1254
01:03:09,911 --> 01:03:12,090
I hope you will.

1255
01:03:13,974 --> 01:03:16,267
Grimshaw, go with Madam La Grange
and do what she tells you.

1256
01:03:16,610 --> 01:03:19,247
You can't mean it, Inspector.
What she asks is too horrible.

1257
01:03:19,669 --> 01:03:20,686
Do what I say.

1258
01:03:22,267 --> 01:03:23,547
God bless you, sir'.

1259
01:03:25,308 --> 01:03:27,447
You will bring them right along?
- Yes.

1260
01:03:48,953 --> 01:03:50,226
The brazenness of the girl.

1261
01:03:50,667 --> 01:03:52,255
Saying she sent Helen for the letters.

1262
01:03:54,142 --> 01:03:55,532
[ Door knocks ]

1263
01:03:59,875 --> 01:04:02,000
I say, Inspector. You are most welcome.

1264
01:04:02,532 --> 01:04:04,162
Can we all go now?
- You shall not.

1265
01:04:05,462 --> 01:04:07,528
I must ask everyone to
return to the other room.

1266
01:04:08,017 --> 01:04:09,837
Look here, you have the guilty party.

1267
01:04:10,222 --> 01:04:12,917
Is there no end to this red tape?
- Thank you, Mr Trent.

1268
01:04:13,260 --> 01:04:16,577
Your assurance that I have the
guilty party gives me a great relief.

1269
01:04:17,207 --> 01:04:18,308
Will you come please?

1270
01:04:26,666 --> 01:04:28,857
I guess that's alright?
- Yes, sir. That is alright.

1271
01:04:29,353 --> 01:04:30,415
Don't be worried.

1272
01:04:30,901 --> 01:04:32,030
You go back to Nellie.

1273
01:04:43,044 --> 01:04:44,221
Please, please.

1274
01:04:45,905 --> 01:04:48,670
Now you will all do as
Madam La Grange asks.

1275
01:04:51,088 --> 01:04:54,718
Now, if you will all
take the same places.

1276
01:05:00,189 --> 01:05:01,329
Look here, everyone.

1277
01:05:01,687 --> 01:05:03,957
We should refuse to continue
with this tomfoolery.

1278
01:05:04,815 --> 01:05:08,101
I think this is a beastly outrage.
Sir Roscoe, must we continue with this?

1279
01:05:08,444 --> 01:05:11,319
Inspector, is this necessary?
- Quite necessary.

1280
01:05:17,030 --> 01:05:19,501
Mr Standish, your demonstration
is unnecessary.

1281
01:05:19,880 --> 01:05:21,879
Unnecessary? Unnecessary?

1282
01:05:22,516 --> 01:05:23,355
I say, sir.

1283
01:05:23,785 --> 01:05:25,437
That is the dead body of Edward Wales.

1284
01:05:26,183 --> 01:05:28,536
Inspector, this is a little too much.
It's too much.

1285
01:05:29,149 --> 01:05:30,582
You really are going too far.

1286
01:05:30,949 --> 01:05:33,089
We can't bear this.
We really can't stand it.

1287
01:05:34,423 --> 01:05:35,067
Sure.

1288
01:05:35,606 --> 01:05:36,541
The innocent.

1289
01:05:37,062 --> 01:05:39,153
Need have no fear of the dead.

1290
01:05:40,906 --> 01:05:41,499
No.

1291
01:05:42,455 --> 01:05:44,805
If you will all sit down.

1292
01:05:46,314 --> 01:05:47,492
Please be seated.

1293
01:05:54,305 --> 01:05:55,611
This is horrible.

1294
01:05:56,031 --> 01:05:56,823
Horrible.

1295
01:05:57,154 --> 01:05:59,705
Father, must I? Must I sit here?

1296
01:06:00,102 --> 01:06:00,892
Inspector.

1297
01:06:01,114 --> 01:06:02,934
Is is necessary for my
daughter to sit there?

1298
01:06:03,335 --> 01:06:04,036
Please.

1299
01:06:04,282 --> 01:06:05,011
Why not?

1300
01:06:05,789 --> 01:06:08,327
The innocent need have no fear.

1301
01:06:09,297 --> 01:06:11,896
My Nellie will hold his other hand.

1302
01:06:15,801 --> 01:06:16,771
Now, Inspector.

1303
01:06:18,202 --> 01:06:19,883
Please close the door.

1304
01:06:21,796 --> 01:06:22,468
I say.

1305
01:06:22,798 --> 01:06:25,758
I say. We're not going to sit
in the dark with that, are we?

1306
01:06:26,309 --> 01:06:28,147
This is dreadful. Dreadful.

1307
01:06:30,913 --> 01:06:31,693
No.

1308
01:06:33,277 --> 01:06:35,431
If you will all join hands.

1309
01:06:40,475 --> 01:06:43,820
Now just keep your minds clear.

1310
01:06:45,322 --> 01:06:48,435
That is all you have to do.

1311
01:06:51,462 --> 01:06:52,285
Now, sir.

1312
01:06:52,891 --> 01:06:54,617
You can put out the light.

1313
01:07:12,209 --> 01:07:14,040
Oh, this is horrible. Horrible.

1314
01:07:21,544 --> 01:07:22,802
A message.

1315
01:07:24,225 --> 01:07:25,355
Has come.

1316
01:07:28,380 --> 01:07:30,392
You, that is hiding.

1317
01:07:31,500 --> 01:07:32,553
Come out.

1318
01:07:34,152 --> 01:07:35,759
You, that is skulking.

1319
01:07:37,497 --> 01:07:38,438
Come out.

1320
01:07:41,352 --> 01:07:42,707
I call.

1321
01:07:43,673 --> 01:07:45,023
On the spirit.

1322
01:07:45,846 --> 01:07:47,824
Of Edward Wales.

1323
01:07:50,387 --> 01:07:51,782
I call.

1324
01:07:53,098 --> 01:07:57,245
On the spirit of Edward Wales.

1325
01:07:59,652 --> 01:08:00,421
<i>I</i>.

1326
01:08:02,194 --> 01:08:02,904
<i>Am</i>.

1327
01:08:03,861 --> 01:08:04,660
<i>Trying</i>.

1328
01:08:06,086 --> 01:08:08,386
<i>To reach</i>.

1329
01:08:09,485 --> 01:08:10,679
<i>You</i>.

1330
01:08:13,137 --> 01:08:14,637
<i>I am</i>.

1331
01:08:16,605 --> 01:08:19,225
<i>Far .. away</i>.

1332
01:08:20,373 --> 01:08:22,676
That is .. that is Wales' voice.

1333
01:08:23,938 --> 01:08:26,275
But Wales .. is dead.

1334
01:08:31,968 --> 01:08:33,868
<i>I come</i>.

1335
01:08:35,976 --> 01:08:38,676
<i>A long way</i>.

1336
01:08:41,402 --> 01:08:43,125
He is moving.

1337
01:08:43,555 --> 01:08:46,126
I can't stand it. I can't stand it!

1338
01:08:49,591 --> 01:08:50,350
Mother.

1339
01:08:50,752 --> 01:08:53,270
Mother. He is taking his hand away.

1340
01:08:55,150 --> 01:08:56,321
<i>Look</i>.

1341
01:09:00,140 --> 01:09:01,381
<i>Look</i>.

1342
01:09:14,758 --> 01:09:16,094
Mrs Eastwood. Mary. My hand.

1343
01:09:16,449 --> 01:09:17,880
You are touching my hand.

1344
01:09:23,128 --> 01:09:24,162
Take him away.

1345
01:09:24,597 --> 01:09:26,394
Take him away. I did it, I did it.

1346
01:09:26,749 --> 01:09:27,624
I did it!

1347
01:09:28,206 --> 01:09:28,964
I did it.

1348
01:09:31,115 --> 01:09:31,998
Grimshaw.

1349
01:09:32,749 --> 01:09:33,679
Yes, Inspector?

1350
01:09:34,027 --> 01:09:35,968
Get ready to take down
Mrs Eastwood's confession.

1351
01:09:36,521 --> 01:09:37,200
No.

1352
01:09:41,687 --> 01:09:45,375
You believed Wales was the only one who
could get the message from Spencer Lee.

1353
01:09:46,589 --> 01:09:49,329
You killed Wales to prevent that.

1354
01:09:49,985 --> 01:09:51,915
Yes. And you killed Spencer Lee.

1355
01:09:53,028 --> 01:09:53,643
Why?

1356
01:09:56,205 --> 01:09:57,079
I had to.

1357
01:09:58,354 --> 01:09:59,609
I had to. I had to.

1358
01:10:01,300 --> 01:10:02,332
He deserved it.

1359
01:10:03,019 --> 01:10:04,890
Oh, he deserved it!

1360
01:10:09,351 --> 01:10:10,570
Only one thing mattered.

1361
01:10:11,621 --> 01:10:14,086
That my husband had gone
to London on business.

1362
01:10:15,290 --> 01:10:17,273
But he hasn't, he hasn't, he hasn't.

1363
01:10:17,781 --> 01:10:20,379
He found out about Spencer and me.

1364
01:10:21,373 --> 01:10:23,014
And he left me.

1365
01:10:25,731 --> 01:10:28,563
I was there with him that day
in his room when Nellie came.

1366
01:10:32,749 --> 01:10:36,028
Oh, the beast! The rotten, rotten beast.

1367
01:10:39,648 --> 01:10:41,250
Knowing that I was there hiding.

1368
01:10:43,009 --> 01:10:44,547
He tried to make love to Nellie.

1369
01:10:46,375 --> 01:10:47,480
Then she left.

1370
01:10:49,600 --> 01:10:50,663
I went crazy.

1371
01:10:51,390 --> 01:10:52,465
I went mad.

1372
01:10:53,032 --> 01:10:55,818
I grabbed the knife in his
desk and I stabbed him.

1373
01:10:56,196 --> 01:10:57,107
I killed him!

1374
01:10:58,286 --> 01:11:00,698
That's enough. That's enough. Please.

1375
01:11:01,425 --> 01:11:03,112
You don't have to know any more.

1376
01:11:03,526 --> 01:11:06,211
You don't have to know any more.

1377
01:11:06,750 --> 01:11:09,212
Please. You don't have to know any more.

1378
01:11:11,284 --> 01:11:13,039
That chair. Where is Richard?

1379
01:11:13,775 --> 01:11:15,708
That chair was empty when
I turned on the light.

1380
01:11:16,159 --> 01:11:16,946
Sure, sir.

1381
01:11:17,531 --> 01:11:21,952
It was Mr Richard who put the
cane in poor Mr Wales' sleeve.

1382
01:11:22,662 --> 01:11:24,968
So he would point his arm in the air.

1383
01:11:25,645 --> 01:11:26,332
I see.

1384
01:11:27,854 --> 01:11:28,918
Nellie darling.

1385
01:11:32,588 --> 01:11:33,533
Excuse me, sir.

1386
01:11:34,030 --> 01:11:35,435
Father. Father.

1387
01:11:36,231 --> 01:11:37,541
I lied about Nellie.

1388
01:11:38,359 --> 01:11:40,302
I lied about those letters.

1389
01:11:41,023 --> 01:11:42,041
I know, my dear.

1390
01:11:43,222 --> 01:11:43,923
I know.

1391
01:11:52,322 --> 01:11:53,499
Oh Nellie.

1392
01:11:54,769 --> 01:11:55,711
Laughing-Eyes.

1393
01:11:57,189 --> 01:11:59,843
Are they going to live
happily ever after?

1394
01:12:00,635 --> 01:12:01,492
Remember.

1395
01:12:04,609 --> 01:12:05,989
And one for Yes.

1396
01:12:07,266 --> 01:12:08,110
[ One rap. ]

1397
01:12:09,282 --> 01:12:10,118
Richard.

1398
01:12:10,745 --> 01:12:12,060
I love you so.

1399
01:12:19,364 --> 01:12:20,166
..s-d..
